The Syntaxity puzzle games are good (and this is IMO the best one), except for when they hide the next step in a nearly invisible part of the screen. The graphics are kind of surreal, like someone photoshopped different photographs together to make a scene, but I kind of like them. They also all require you to pay extra on top of the game cost for hints and fast travel, which is a bit cheeky but I've had no issues finishing the games without them. For the price of a coffee they're worth it.

Too intrusive - Had to uninstall because it required unusual permission to access my phone's files. No other games required this. My spouse is a computer analyst, and said that the game was not safe,  and should not require access to my files, except for the purpose of obtaining information to sell. I regret buying. Especially since I never got to play it.  In response: I have installed larger games from Google Play that did NOT require these permissions. I can list 10 at least. And they were installed on this very phone. What you say is untrue.
replyContent: Hello, Our games absolutely do not access any information on users devices. The "Access to Storage" permission is required by Google when the size of the game is over 100MB and a separate Expansion File must be downloaded to install the game. More information can be found here: https://developer.android.com/google/play/expansion-files.html

content: Bigger than the programmers previous ventures, I still have mixed feelings about the game. There are some clever & varied puzzles in pleasant surroundings, no hidden object scenes, hurrah! Yet somehow, in a Myst kind of way, it's a lonely experience with much backtracking that still has u searching for an item to use elsewhere, the task being to remember! The game is overpriced too but still well constructed, quick loading, saving & no crashing. A good time waster but still room for improvement.
Too much back and forth. Puzzle play could benefit from more linear play. Fast travel was nice, however, I want to spend more time solving and less time backtracking.

I love Lone Wolf games. Your games just keep getting better and better! I always get my money's worth and then some! Thank you so much for listening to your customers and implementing their suggestions. I love the transport feature! There were still some puzzles that could have used a skip button though.... The only other thing I would suggest is breaking up the walkthrough somehow. I had to use the walkthrough for 2 different puzzles. It was really tough to find just the right place in the walkthrough without seeing the solutions for puzzles in areas I hadn't even seen yet.

Another excellent game from Lone Wolf.  One of the best things about it is that you don't have wade through loads of ads every time you start the game.  I'd have liked the ending to have been a little more rewarding, but this doesn't detract from the game.  Great stuff, and can't wait for the next one!

I'm a huge fan of adventure brain games. This one was loads of fun. Definitely worth the small amount of money it costs.    Puzzles are hard enough to require some thought, but not so hard as to be unsolvable. Hint book is just enough to set you on the right path, mostly when you're not sure which world to head to next, but not so revealing as to solve the puzzles for you. There are LOADS of puzzles to do, and a variety of worlds to explore. Nice graphics as well.   The walk through is good if you're completely stuck. The one thing that would have been nice on the walk through would be a TOC with the scene numbers so you can jump right to the puzzle causing problems rather than skip around looking for help.   Very happy I found Lone Wolf games. Will definitely download more.   One tip for anyone doing this game: I keep a running list of puzzles to solve and the scene numbers where they can be found. It helped me TONS when I found a piece and needed to jump to a scene on another world to refer to my list. Just a fwiw tip. :)
replyContent: Wow! Thank you so much for your review, so great to hear you enjoyed the game :)
